<DOC><DOCNO> AP880622-0128 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-22-88 1225EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-SAfrica-Explosion     06-22 0210</FIRST><SECOND>PM-SAfrica-Explosion,0217</SECOND><HEAD>At Least 10 Injured in Johannesburg Explosion</HEAD><DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An bomb blast destroyed avideo game and pinball arcade in downtown Johannesburg, injuring atleast 10 people, police said.   The facade of the Winning Games Center was blown out by theexplosion at 2:06 p.m. and a fire flared briefly before it was putout, they said.   Police Col. Frans Malherbe said the injured included six blacks,one white and three people of Indian descent, including thepregnant woman, her husband and their daughter.   Malherbe said four of the victims were seriously hurt.   Witnesses said one woman was knocked off her feet by the blastand appeared seriously injured. Police said the blast was caused byan explosive device known as a limpet mine.   The arcade is located on the ground floor of an apartmentbuilding. Residents were ordered to evacuate as police investigated.   More than two dozen bombing and hand grenade attacks in SouthAfrica this year have killed 14 people.   The government has blamed the attacks on the outlawed AfricanNational Congress, the only guerrilla movement fighting the whiteSouth African government. The ANC has not claimed responsibilityfor the various attacks, but has said it plans to intensify itsguerrilla operations.</TEXT></DOC>